[We must await the exhumation of the buried carcasses and proper necropsies for formal IVRI confirmation of the comment of apparent stab wounds, but at this point, the lack of microbiological and epidemiologic evidence of anthrax, and in the absence of any other cause of death, it is highly probable that a crime was committed. Personally, if the deer had died of anthrax, I would expect to see more bloating of the 4 carcasses in the picture; abdominal bloating is very characteristic of anthrax carcasses.

The chital, cheetal, or axis deer is a beautiful beast; see: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cheetal, which only makes this abominable act even more inexcusable, and of national embarrassment, all in all, a poor show.

Chhattisgarh is to the immediate west of Orissa on the eastern side of India; see: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_physio-2001.jpg. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1pSH.]
